Rapper Emeka Akumefule aka Blaqbonez has recounted how her mother forced him to donate the first N200,000 he made as an upcoming artist to a pastor. The 25-year-old controversial rapper made this revelation on Twitter while reminiscing on his days of humble beginnings. “When I made my first 200k and I wanted to buy studio equipment, my mum carried me to go and give the pastor as first fruit,” he said. Blaqbonez also recalled how he fainted when the computer he was using crashed after he had recorded his songs.   Mercy Aigbe’s ex-husband, Lanre Gentry breaks silence     Bovi’s wife recounts near death experience with ectopic…     Court discharges De General of drug trafficking charges   - Advertisement - “The first mixtape I recorded, the sound engineer called me to say his system crashed and everything was lost. I fell to the ground on the main road in tears because Omo I was traveling from OAU to Lagos every weekend to record it. “I took the longest road to success in this music thing, I fucking dropped 8 mixtapes, when I look back, it doesn’t make sense that I didn’t give up. “At some points, I had to produce, mix, and master my shit because I was dropping every week, like 50 songs a year. Which money I go use pay people?”